{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"E1 DESCOPE NOTE (2026-07-16): E1's finding-adjudication TP/FP corpus was INVALIDATED (tool-less, plan-truncated labeling that doesn't match the whole-plan/code-grounded/agentic production gate; ~79 percent contaminated) and DESCOPED — the independent human-adjudicated gold set is parked as idea e59d-c078-724d-46e5. E1 still delivers the VALID outcome corpus + finding sample. This story (E6) draws its ~50 findings from the E1 adjudication corpus's SAMPLE (the capability-assertion cohort) and RE-JUDGES them to measure self-consistency — it uses the finding SAMPLE, which SURVIVES, NOT the invalid TP/FP labels. UNAFFECTED. It could later be ENRICHED into self-consistency-vs-truth by the idea's human gold set."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784238639520781001,"uuid":"bb1f8053-b6a7-4b5f-9678-21c093069bfc"}